name: A snowstorm of stars
description:
In this sparkling Hubble image, Sun-like stars appear yellow-white and the reddish stars are bright giants that are in the final stages of their lives.

Name:	Messier 79
Type:	Milky Way : Star : Grouping : Cluster : Globular
Distance:	40000 light years
Constellation:	Lepus
Category:	Star Clusters

3,629 editions for the known 3,629 planetary systems to date.

Credit: ESA/Hubble/NASA
